      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇮🇳 India - Operation kills a wanted terrorist.</strong> India’s “Operation Sindoor” killed Abdul Rauf Azhar, a top Jaish-e-Mohammed commander linked to the 2002 beheading of journalist Daniel Pearl. Targeting terror hideouts across Pakistan, the strikes reportedly killed nearly 100 militants. India framed the operation as part of the global fight against terrorism (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-worldwide-7-terrorist-annihilated" target="_blank">terrorist annihilated</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇮🇷 Iran - Won’t halt.</strong>  Iran vowed to continue enriching uranium despite US demands, ahead of expected nuclear talks in Rome. FM Abbas Araghchi reiterated that enrichment would proceed with or without an agreement. Tensions remain high as Iran enriches uranium up to 60%, nearing weapons-grade levels, while the US and Israel warn of potential military measures if diplomacy fails (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-worldwide-8-no-quitters-here" target="_blank">no quitters here</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇸🇪 Sweden - Summons ambassador.</strong> Sweden summoned Israel’s ambassador, demanding immediate permission to provide aid to Gaza amid a worsening humanitarian crisis. Criticizing Israel’s military campaign, the Swedish foreign ministry called the blockade “indefensible.” Israel blocked aid from entering the besieged coastal enclave, before allowing in a small amount (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-worldwide-9-dent-in-eu-israel-relations" target="_blank">dent in EU-Israel relations</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇨🇳 China - Cashing in on advance.</strong> 
           75 poorest nations face a record $22B in liability repayments to China in 2025, primarily from liabilities associated with the Belt and Road Initiative. These repayments threaten essential domestic spending and may increase Beijing’s political leverage. China, seen more as a collector than a lender, faces pressure amid its economic slowdown (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-worldwide-10-more-about-the-report" target="_blank">more about the report</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇰🇪 Kenya - Backs Morocco.</strong> 
            Kenya announced support for Morocco’s autonomy plan for Western Sahara, calling it the credible fix to the decades-long conflict. During a visit to Rabat, Kenya also opened an embassy and agreed to deepen trade and cooperation. Morocco will boost its fertilizer exports to Kenya, while Kenya aims to increase its exports of tea, coffee, and other agricultural products (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-worldwide-11-kenyan-moroccan-relations" target="_blank">Kenyan-Moroccan relations</a>).  
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
