          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
     How was St. Petersburg founded?
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/peter-the-great-new-russian-capital-western-outlet-history.jpg" alt="Peter ruthlessly disregarded practical considerations and human life in his determination to create a new capital for himself and a Russian outlet to the West" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
          <i>Peter ruthlessly disregarded practical considerations and humans in his determination to create a capital for himself and a Russian outlet to the West. Credits: History</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">     
        <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-foundations-h1-12-st-petersburg" target="_blank">St. Petersburg</a> was founded by Tsar Peter the Great in 1703 and sits on swampy land by the River Neva. Peter the Great sought a "window to Europe" as a port and a capital to replace Moscow. He spent a lot of time in the Netherlands learning how to build ships. During his time in Europe, he envisioned Russia having a city with similar amenities to those of Paris and Amsterdam. 
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      Building the city came at a tremendous <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-may-25-foundations-h1-13-human-expense" target="_blank">human expense</a>. Many of the conscripted peasants died from disease, starvation, and harsh conditions. This earned the city the nickname "City Built on Bones." Peter brought in foreign architects to design grand boulevards, canals, and neoclassical buildings, such as the Peter and Paul Fortress.</p>
       <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Despite pushback, he compelled nobles, merchants, and artisans to relocate to the city and construct homes. The city represented the New Russia that Peter aimed to create. It grew into one of Europe’s most remarkable cities, showcasing imperial ambition, urban planning, and cultural change.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        This city, like most cities in Russia, the CIS countries, Europe, and America, has its own holiday, the birthday of St. Petersburg, which falls on May 27th.</p>
       </mj-text>
